	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Pretty much, except that the sprite will still show through transparent parts of the mountain.
<br />
<br />In graphics programming for 2D game consoles, the terms "Z", "priority", and "layering" have similar meanings. On the NES, a sprite whose priority bit is turned on will appear "behind" opaque parts of the background, but the priority bit doesn't affect layering between one sprite and another.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


